      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/46",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ اَلرَّجُلُ يَشْتَرِي اَلْمَمْلُوكَ وَ مَالَهُ فَقَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ\" قُلْتُ فَيَكُونُ مَالُ اَلْمَمْلُوكِ أَكْثَرَ مِمَّا اِشْتَرَاهُ بِهِ فَقَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3817 - Zurara narrated: \"I said to Abu Abdullah (as): A man buys a slave along with his wealth.\nImam (as) replied: 'There is no harm in it.'\nI asked: 'What if the wealth of the slave is greater than the price he was purchased for?'\nImam (as) replied: 'There is no harm in it.'"
        ]
      }
    },
